          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 16</h1><p><strong>Questions 31 - 35</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A, B or C</strong>.</p><p>31 On which area of business does the lecturer say she will focus in her analysis of the Channel Tunnel?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    The property business</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    The travel business</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    The foreign trade business</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>32 In 1802, what did Albert Mathieu suggest should be built in the middle of the English Channel to help travel between the United Kingdom and France?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    A man-made island</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Special ships</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    A tower</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>33 Which country was worried about a connection between France and the United Kingdom?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    The United Kingdom</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    France</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Holland</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>34 When did money problems cause a break in the twentieth-century’s plans for building the tunnel?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    1974</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    1976</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    1985</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>35 Which route (A, B or C) shown on the map below most accurately shows the location of the Channel Tunnel?</p>",
